Hispaniola. They began that system of cruelty towards the
natives, which in a few years almost depopulated that island,
and was afterwards pursued by Cortez, Pizarro and others, in
all the first settlements in Spanish America.</p>
<p>Boyle was a fanatical priest who accompanied Ovando, and,
under pretence of christianizing the natives by the sword,
gave the sanction of the church to the most shocking and extensive
scenes of slaughter.</p></note> Boyle,</l>
